413
00:29:06.454 --> 00:29:09.405
How did he hold up an entire mountain?

414
00:29:09.430 --> 00:29:13.429
His chi is strong. like
nothing I've ever felt.

415
00:29:13.896 --> 00:29:18.697
Hey. Avatar. you think this guy beat
your record for longest frozen airbender?

416
00:29:18.746 --> 00:29:21.697
Yeah.
How long do you think he was in that ice?

417
00:29:21.896 --> 00:29:25.717
I don't know. His tattoos look ancient.

418
00:29:26.366 --> 00:29:27.717
He's been in there a long time.

419
00:29:27.718 --> 00:29:29.717
He smells good for an old guy.

420
00:29:29.718 --> 00:29:30.718
Ew.

421
00:29:30.916 --> 00:29:32.717
What? My senses tell me
this guy is pretty attractive.

422
00:29:32.718 --> 00:29:33.743
-Toph! -Someone else confirmed.

423
00:29:33.767 --> 00:29:34.717
This is serious.

424
00:29:34.767 --> 00:29:35.717
What does "attractive" even mean?

425
00:29:35.718 --> 00:29:37.717
Just give me a straight confirmation.

426
00:29:37.718 --> 00:29:38.717
Is he attractive?

427
00:29:38.718 --> 00:29:39.718
He's very attractive.

428
00:29:40.016 --> 00:29:41.717
Huh?

429
00:29:41.816 --> 00:29:44.737
What? He is.
It's all in the bone structure.

430
00:29:45.258 --> 00:29:46.417
No.

431
00:29:47.836 --> 00:29:48.669
No.

432
00:29:49.306 --> 00:29:49.899
No!

433
00:29:49.924 --> 00:29:51.923
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Hey.

434
00:29:51.948 --> 00:29:53.947
Easy. You're safe.

435
00:29:56.727 --> 00:29:57.639
♪♪ Earthbender!

436
00:29:57.728 --> 00:29:59.078
No. no. no. We're all friends here.

437
00:29:59.371 --> 00:30:00.371
It's okay.

438
00:30:00.719 --> 00:30:03.590
Someone woke up on the
wrong side of the mountain.

439
00:30:04.088 --> 00:30:06.589
Where is she?

440
00:30:06.739 --> 00:30:08.490
Where is Avatar Sonam?

441
00:30:08.922 --> 00:30:10.623
You knew Sonam?

442
00:30:11.522 --> 00:30:12.623
Who are you?

443
00:30:13.822 --> 00:30:18.623
I don't know how to explain it. but
you've been asleep for a long time.

444
00:30:19.180 --> 00:30:20.556
I'm the Avatar now.

445
00:30:21.105 --> 00:30:22.556
I'm Aang.

446
00:30:23.526 --> 00:30:25.387
If you're the Avatar...

447
00:30:25.511 --> 00:30:30.777
then Sonam.

448
00:30:31.076 --> 00:30:33.944
Well. Sonim might be
long gone. but on the

449
00:30:33.945 --> 00:30:36.777
bright side. you woke
up at the perfect time.

450
00:30:36.778 --> 00:30:39.777
Everyone will be amazed
to see another Airbender.

451
00:30:40.076 --> 00:30:42.777
Aang's not the last one anymore.

452
00:30:43.509 --> 00:30:45.630
What do you mean. "last"?

453
00:30:45.798 --> 00:30:48.797
Oh.

454
00:30:50.028 --> 00:30:51.529
The Air Nomads.

455
00:30:52.329 --> 00:30:54.630
They've been wiped out.

456
00:30:55.496 --> 00:30:57.797
There's only me.

457
00:30:58.064 --> 00:31:00.063
No.

458
00:31:00.446 --> 00:31:02.697
Sonam's Staff. do you have it?

459
00:31:03.929 --> 00:31:04.750
It's our only hope now.

460
00:31:05.747 --> 00:31:07.391
What do you mean?

461
00:31:07.416 --> 00:31:08.817
I thought it was a weapon.

462
00:31:10.216 --> 00:31:11.817
The staff is no weapon.

463
00:31:12.616 --> 00:31:14.817
It is a gift.

464
00:31:16.191 --> 00:31:20.817
With it. Sonam was able to channel
the vast power of the spirit world.

465
00:31:21.916 --> 00:31:24.817
It was this power that
allowed Jirana to flourish.

466
00:31:25.066 --> 00:31:29.837
The greatest city in the
world. an Air Nomad utopia.

467
00:31:30.411 --> 00:31:33.837
where Sonim presided
over a golden age of balance.

468
00:31:33.838 --> 00:31:37.837
and where I devoted
my life to serving her.

469
00:31:38.136 --> 00:31:41.862
In return. she raised me
up and used her staff to give

470
00:31:41.863 --> 00:31:46.857
me. a lowly non-Bender.
the power to bend the air.

471
00:31:47.755 --> 00:31:50.656
I was the first. but I
would not be the last.

472
00:31:51.357 --> 00:31:55.285
She filled the skies with
Airbenders. and we flew

473
00:31:55.310 --> 00:31:59.381
by her side. spreading
peace across the world.

474
00:32:07.015 --> 00:32:09.586
Aang. are you okay?

475
00:32:10.852 --> 00:32:13.603
Sonim used the staff to
give people Airbending.

476
00:32:14.493 --> 00:32:16.544
If we found it.

477
00:32:17.583 --> 00:32:19.634
I could bring Airbending back to the world.

478
00:32:20.592 --> 00:32:21.593
This is incredible.

479
00:32:21.618 --> 00:32:24.617
There haven't been Airbenders
for over a hundred years.

480
00:32:25.377 --> 00:32:29.398
This is everything you ever wanted. Aang.

481
00:32:30.147 --> 00:32:33.898
We could heal the greatest atrocity
my nation committed in the war.

482
00:32:35.097 --> 00:32:37.898
This could be the final
step to rebuilding the world.

483
00:32:38.297 --> 00:32:39.898
Not if the Denied get there first.

484
00:32:40.297 --> 00:32:41.898
They have the map.

485
00:32:42.597 --> 00:32:43.898
Who are the Denied?

486
00:32:43.947 --> 00:32:45.898
A group of violent non-Benders.

487
00:32:46.297 --> 00:32:47.918
They...they must be after the staff

488
00:32:48.367 --> 00:32:49.918
to give themselves Airbending.

489
00:32:50.767 --> 00:32:51.967
Then there's no time to waste.

490
00:32:52.383 --> 00:32:53.784
There's only one place it could be.

491
00:32:54.218 --> 00:32:55.217
Ready your bison.

492
00:32:55.252 --> 00:32:58.251
We'll need to travel
across the endless ocean.

493
00:32:58.542 --> 00:32:59.918
On the other side of the world?

494
00:33:00.417 --> 00:33:01.918
But there's nothing out there.

495
00:33:01.919 --> 00:33:04.918
There's an island.
The journey will not be easy.

496
00:33:05.267 --> 00:33:06.938
but we can make it.

497
00:33:07.787 --> 00:33:08.938
Then let's get going.

498
00:33:10.027 --> 00:33:12.938
The skies are no place for a water child.

499
00:33:13.027 --> 00:33:14.727
Water child?

500
00:33:15.187 --> 00:33:18.277
Um. I know you just
woke up after thousands

501
00:33:18.278 --> 00:33:20.938
of years. but we do
these things together.

502
00:33:20.939 --> 00:33:22.938
Trust me. we're stronger this way.

503
00:33:23.337 --> 00:33:24.938
Welcome to Team Avatar.

504
00:33:25.587 --> 00:33:26.938
What's your name?

505
00:33:27.487 --> 00:33:29.958
Tagah. My name is Tagah.

506
00:33:32.137 --> 00:33:39.938
♪♪

507
00:33:39.939 --> 00:33:42.938
Just think of it as a big metal air bison.

508
00:33:42.939 --> 00:33:50.938
♪♪

509
00:33:50.939 --> 00:33:54.938
We will travel ancient
paths through the sky.

510
00:33:55.237 --> 00:33:58.078
ones that our people
learned by following the great

511
00:33:58.212 --> 00:34:01.091
air bison herds that long
ago taught us Airbending.

512
00:34:02.098 --> 00:34:07.958
Air currents known only to us.
encircling the great sphere of existence.

513
00:34:07.959 --> 00:34:14.957
allowing us to travel where we wish.
giving us our name. the Air Nomads.

514
00:34:26.977 --> 00:34:34.977
♪♪

515
00:34:36.977 --> 00:34:44.977
♪♪

516
00:34:45.128 --> 00:34:46.977
What's he doing?

517
00:34:47.228 --> 00:34:48.977
He's really feeling that air.

518
00:34:50.078 --> 00:34:51.997
He's navigating by instinct.

519
00:34:52.173 --> 00:34:53.997
What if his instincts are just wrong?

520
00:34:53.998 --> 00:34:56.997
Who needs instincts when
you've got muscles like that?

521
00:34:57.048 --> 00:34:59.255
Or what if his brain is
messed up from being frozen?

522
00:34:59.456 --> 00:35:00.265
Like me?

523
00:35:00.556 --> 00:35:02.264
Uh. no. no!

524
00:35:02.684 --> 00:35:04.998
He was frozen for 5.000 years. okay?

525
00:35:05.098 --> 00:35:06.998
You were frozen for. what. 100?

526
00:35:06.999 --> 00:35:07.999
Okay. that's nothing.

527
00:35:08.173 --> 00:35:11.018
Your brain is...fresh.

528
00:35:11.543 --> 00:35:15.443
Maybe he is a little
old-fashioned. but look at him.

529
00:35:15.468 --> 00:35:17.461
He's so in tune with his
element. he can travel

530
00:35:17.462 --> 00:35:22.018
across the entire ocean
with no map. no instruments.

531
00:35:22.019 --> 00:35:24.018
♪♪

532
00:35:24.019 --> 00:35:25.018
[ Sighs ]

533
00:35:25.019 --> 00:35:27.018
There's so much I can learn from him.

534
00:35:29.238 --> 00:35:37.038
♪♪

535
00:35:37.039 --> 00:35:39.038
[ Chuckles ]

536
00:35:39.039 --> 00:35:42.591
I'd give anything to be able
to see my air bison again.

537
00:35:43.188 --> 00:35:45.415
[ Grunts ]

538
00:35:45.640 --> 00:35:46.619
And now...

539
00:35:47.218 --> 00:35:48.634
to see only one remains.

540
00:35:48.659 --> 00:35:50.469
[ Grunts ]

541
00:35:51.239 --> 00:35:52.404
Aang

542
00:35:53.371 --> 00:35:56.891
You said our people were
wiped out. yet you survived.

543
00:35:57.675 --> 00:35:58.825
How?

544
00:36:00.958 --> 00:36:03.058
I had just found out I was the Avatar.

545
00:36:03.839 --> 00:36:06.061
but the responsibility...

546
00:36:06.419 --> 00:36:08.174
-- it was too much.

547
00:36:09.499 --> 00:36:10.824
So I ran away.

548
00:36:12.358 --> 00:36:16.078
And while I was gone.
the Fire Nation attacked.

549
00:36:16.245 --> 00:36:17.244
[ Sighs ]

550
00:36:17.688 --> 00:36:19.687
They were looking for me.

551
00:36:19.712 --> 00:36:21.539
♪♪

552
00:36:21.697 --> 00:36:22.556
If...

553
00:36:23.190 --> 00:36:24.739
-- if I'd just been there...

554
00:36:25.345 --> 00:36:26.845
Sonam would say.

555
00:36:27.245 --> 00:36:30.045
"Air nomads are formed from the mist.

556
00:36:30.477 --> 00:36:32.977
We walk the world for a moment in time.

557
00:36:33.378 --> 00:36:36.998
Then we return
to the eternal wind."

558
00:36:37.099 --> 00:36:38.099
♪♪

559
00:36:38.230 --> 00:36:40.030
Monk Gyatso taught me that.

560
00:36:40.898 --> 00:36:42.133
We carry the same weight.

561
00:36:42.998 --> 00:36:46.098
a grief no one else could
possibly comprehend.

562
00:36:46.264 --> 00:36:48.546
But you and I can heal the past.

563
00:36:49.065 --> 00:36:56.064
Let me show you how powerful our element
can be when airbenders work together.

564
00:36:57.941 --> 00:36:58.778
♪♪ Aah!

565
00:36:58.779 --> 00:37:00.118
What are you doing?!

566
00:37:00.119 --> 00:37:01.118
Aah!

567
00:37:01.119 --> 00:37:03.118
This is how Sonam taught me!

568
00:37:03.119 --> 00:37:06.118
Feel the energy that tethers us.

569
00:37:06.119 --> 00:37:09.118
[ Gasping ]

570
00:37:09.119 --> 00:37:11.118
[ Laughs ]

571
00:37:11.119 --> 00:37:15.366
The bond between us -- can you feel it?
Use it!

572
00:37:15.466 --> 00:37:17.660
This is amazing!

573
00:37:18.193 --> 00:37:19.171
Yeah!

574
00:37:22.336 --> 00:37:23.457
[ Laughs ] Whoo-hoo!

575
00:37:23.482 --> 00:37:24.777
Oh. yeah!

576
00:37:25.077 --> 00:37:26.138
Human boomerang!

577
00:37:26.305 --> 00:37:27.711
He's actually flying.

578
00:37:28.012 --> 00:37:28.714
So are we.

579
00:37:28.788 --> 00:37:30.139
Whoa! That's my best friend!

580
00:37:30.140 --> 00:37:32.139
That's my best friend!

581
00:37:32.140 --> 00:37:34.139
Now. you throw me!

582
00:37:34.140 --> 00:37:35.139
[ Grunts ]

583
00:37:35.140 --> 00:37:36.140
[ Grunts ]

584
00:37:38.159 --> 00:37:46.159
♪♪

585
00:37:48.159 --> 00:37:56.159
♪♪

586
00:37:56.160 --> 00:38:02.179
♪♪

587
00:38:02.507 --> 00:38:04.506
I had no idea this was possible!

588
00:38:04.531 --> 00:38:06.530
This is only the beginning.

589
00:38:06.555 --> 00:38:14.085
♪♪

590
00:38:14.345 --> 00:38:15.965
I can't believe it.

591
00:38:16.215 --> 00:38:17.865
Airbenders will fill the sky again.

592
00:38:18.766 --> 00:38:21.066
We have been given a great gift --

593
00:38:21.499 --> 00:38:22.999
the chance to redeem ourselves.

594
00:38:23.882 --> 00:38:27.932
You were destined to find
me on that mountain. Aang.

595
00:38:28.765 --> 00:38:30.965
How did you end up there?

596
00:38:34.565 --> 00:38:37.065
The earthbenders had attacked Jirana.

597
00:38:37.299 --> 00:38:40.019
Sonam and I fought
fearlessly. side by side.

598
00:38:40.602 --> 00:38:42.287
We drove them back to Mount Baihu.

599
00:38:42.868 --> 00:38:45.918
and that's the last I remember.

600
00:38:46.835 --> 00:38:48.035
She must have saved your life.

601
00:38:49.035 --> 00:38:52.085
Only an Avatar could
have put you in that sphere.

602
00:38:55.202 --> 00:38:58.072
Aang. can I ask you something?

603
00:38:58.240 --> 00:38:59.240
Of course.

604
00:39:00.089 --> 00:39:03.239
If the Fire Nation
destroyed the Air Nomads.

605
00:39:03.739 --> 00:39:06.939
how can you suffer the
presence of the Fire Lord?

606
00:39:09.388 --> 00:39:11.038
Zuko is a friend and an ally.

607
00:39:11.972 --> 00:39:15.072
He turned against his own
father to help me end the war.

608
00:39:15.439 --> 00:39:18.059
Yet he wears the crown himself now.

609
00:39:18.675 --> 00:39:22.025
Fire. by its nature. burns. Aang.

610
00:39:22.408 --> 00:39:24.058
Our kind have always suffered

611
00:39:24.083 --> 00:39:26.983
at the hands of the other elements.

612
00:39:27.391 --> 00:39:29.091
That's why we built Republic City --

613
00:39:29.792 --> 00:39:31.992
to show the world that
if we listen to each other.

614
00:39:32.525 --> 00:39:36.125
we can all live together in peace.

615
00:39:36.333 --> 00:39:41.078
And once we bring back
airbenders. it'll be complete.

616
00:39:43.912 --> 00:39:45.232
When everyone stuck to their own.

617
00:39:46.028 --> 00:39:48.078
the whole world was nearly torn apart.

618
00:39:49.178 --> 00:39:53.078
And besides. Katara. Sokka. Zuko. Toph.

619
00:39:53.662 --> 00:39:55.112
they're my family now.

620
00:39:56.646 --> 00:39:59.166
I want to live in a world
where we can all be together.

621
00:40:00.998 --> 00:40:04.098
You remind me so much of Sonam.

622
00:40:08.281 --> 00:40:09.333
It's the Avatar.

623
00:40:09.990 --> 00:40:11.667
And this time. he's got
his friends with him.

624
00:40:12.160 --> 00:40:13.466
That's the Fire Lord's airship.

625
00:40:13.748 --> 00:40:14.598
How'd they get ahead of us?

626
00:40:14.828 --> 00:40:16.299
They don't even have the map.

627
00:40:16.757 --> 00:40:18.785
We can't risk him
getting to the staff first.

628
00:40:19.017 --> 00:40:19.645
Kill him.

629
00:40:19.851 --> 00:40:21.087
But he spared our lives.

630
00:40:21.594 --> 00:40:25.569
And how many Countless were killed in
the hundred years waiting for his return?

631
00:40:25.594 --> 00:40:28.328
Where was he when
your family was wiped out?

632
00:40:28.461 --> 00:40:31.537
If we want anything to change.
we need what the benders have...

633
00:40:31.750 --> 00:40:32.397
-- power.

634
00:40:40.951 --> 00:40:42.951
Fire!

635
00:40:48.298 --> 00:40:49.656
It's the Denied.

636
00:40:52.095 --> 00:40:54.236
Uh. we are definitely under attack.

637
00:40:55.719 --> 00:40:57.499
Tear them to shreds.

638
00:41:10.168 --> 00:41:12.213
Is he crushing the ship?

639
00:41:14.027 --> 00:41:14.990
Tagah?

640
00:41:15.817 --> 00:41:17.816
Tagah. stop!

641
00:41:42.658 --> 00:41:43.788
We're here.

642
00:41:45.962 --> 00:41:47.421
The Immortal Storm.

643
00:41:48.179 --> 00:41:49.264
Oh. no.

644
00:41:54.854 --> 00:41:56.990
There has to be another way around.

645
00:41:57.015 --> 00:41:57.506
No!

646
00:41:57.531 --> 00:41:59.928
Together. you and I can
clear a path for the ship.

647
00:41:59.953 --> 00:42:01.952
But we have to go now.

648
00:42:01.977 --> 00:42:04.976
Aang. trust me.

649
00:42:07.710 --> 00:42:10.146
Uh. maybe now's a good time to turn back.

650
00:42:10.171 --> 00:42:12.170
I don't think that's an option anymore.

651
00:42:12.195 --> 00:42:14.194
Where are they going?

652
00:42:22.423 --> 00:42:24.467
The engine's out.
We're losing air pressure.

653
00:42:30.622 --> 00:42:31.800
Katara. Toph. come with me.

654
00:42:31.825 --> 00:42:32.609
What about me?

655
00:42:32.634 --> 00:42:33.633
Take the wheel.

656
00:42:33.658 --> 00:42:36.657
What? I've only ever
crashed Fire Nation airships.

657
00:42:38.639 --> 00:42:39.681
Okay. let's see. Here's our rudder.

658
00:42:39.706 --> 00:42:41.705
This is the elevator. There's our ballast.

659
00:42:41.730 --> 00:42:44.406
And there's the giant tornado
that's going to kill us all.

660
00:42:47.639 --> 00:42:49.267
Follow my lead.

661
00:43:00.178 --> 00:43:01.320
Work with me.

662
00:43:01.387 --> 00:43:02.688
Just like I showed you.

663
00:43:03.320 --> 00:43:04.320
We can harness the air.

664
00:43:14.827 --> 00:43:17.320
Yes! That's it. Aang. Keep going.

665
00:43:29.964 --> 00:43:31.131
Got it.

666
00:43:34.320 --> 00:43:36.320
Zuko! Zuko!

667
00:43:36.321 --> 00:43:39.320
Aang and Tagah are destroying
tornadoes. but there's too many!

668
00:43:39.321 --> 00:43:41.320
And they're everywhere!

669
00:43:41.321 --> 00:43:43.320
Just steer the ship. Don't lose Aang.

670
00:43:43.321 --> 00:43:46.320
It's not that easy. especially
when everything is sideways.

671
00:43:46.321 --> 00:43:48.320
Okay. left!

672
00:43:57.452 --> 00:43:58.320
I did it!

673
00:43:59.587 --> 00:44:01.586
Right!

674
00:44:09.019 --> 00:44:11.232
Oh no. we're falling behind!

675
00:44:12.071 --> 00:44:14.736
I'm losing sight of them.
We have to go back.

676
00:44:14.761 --> 00:44:18.760
Trust in your friends. They won't
make it if we don't clear a path.

677
00:44:32.012 --> 00:44:34.320
Zuko. we're going to crash into the sea!

678
00:44:34.321 --> 00:44:37.320
When I give you the signal.
pull the lever next to the wheel.

679
00:44:41.563 --> 00:44:43.320
We're going to crash! We're going to crash!

680
00:44:43.754 --> 00:44:45.753
Katara?

681
00:45:04.853 --> 00:45:06.629
Give me the signal! Give me the signal!

682
00:45:11.371 --> 00:45:12.310
Closed!

683
00:45:13.830 --> 00:45:15.513
Sokka. now!

684
00:45:15.654 --> 00:45:17.653
Here we go!

685
00:45:39.451 --> 00:45:41.451
Katara! We did it!

686
00:45:42.676 --> 00:45:43.957
What were you thinking?

687
00:45:44.016 --> 00:45:45.927
I was clearing the
tornadoes to make a path.

688
00:45:45.952 --> 00:45:48.455
The ship almost crashed. Aang.
We could have died.

689
00:45:48.513 --> 00:45:51.265
And what if you got yourself killed?
You're the Avatar.

690
00:45:51.373 --> 00:45:54.263
This is too risky.
We need to turn back now.

691
00:45:54.296 --> 00:45:55.103
No!

692
00:45:55.556 --> 00:45:56.929
We're almost there.

693
00:45:57.154 --> 00:45:59.225
We just need to get
to the eye of the storm.

694
00:46:00.116 --> 00:46:01.314
Aang. no!

695
00:46:01.339 --> 00:46:02.843
This is too dangerous.

696
00:46:02.868 --> 00:46:05.530
The staff is out there.
The denied are after it.

697
00:46:05.632 --> 00:46:08.048
Do you really believe that they
could make it through the storm?

698
00:46:08.122 --> 00:46:11.285
We're nearly there.
That staff can bring back my people.

699
00:46:11.480 --> 00:46:13.170
I understand how much
you want that. but...

700
00:46:13.195 --> 00:46:15.032
You don't understand.
None of you do.

701
00:46:16.637 --> 00:46:17.738
Aang...

702
00:46:19.727 --> 00:46:21.612
We push forward.

703
00:46:24.827 --> 00:46:26.250
If we generate enough air.

704
00:46:26.275 --> 00:46:28.275
we can push our way through.

705
00:47:13.088 --> 00:47:14.123
We're alive?

706
00:47:14.491 --> 00:47:17.041
We made it through. Thank you. Tagah.

707
00:47:17.199 --> 00:47:20.099
It was you. Aang.
We're here because of you.

708
00:47:20.124 --> 00:47:21.889
Yeah. we're having a good time. too.

709
00:47:21.914 --> 00:47:24.199
You could have told us we were
flying into the Immortal Storm.

710
00:47:24.224 --> 00:47:27.111
I know it was dangerous.
but we had to risk it.

711
00:47:27.136 --> 00:47:28.269
We? [ laugh ]

712
00:47:28.294 --> 00:47:30.086
I don't remember when "WE"
took a vote on that.

713
00:47:30.522 --> 00:47:32.366
There wasn't time. I had to make a call.

714
00:47:32.391 --> 00:47:34.390
Friends. please. don't blame Aang.

715
00:47:34.787 --> 00:47:37.887
This is all my fault.
I knew this would be difficult.

716
00:47:39.120 --> 00:47:41.220
But Aang believed in
your strength as a team.

717
00:47:41.854 --> 00:47:43.254
And I'm honored to be a part of it.

718
00:47:49.604 --> 00:47:51.782
I forgive you. Tagah.

719
00:47:51.903 --> 00:47:53.314
Everyone. look.

720
00:47:54.938 --> 00:47:59.109
These islands... they were... lion turtles.

721
00:48:00.875 --> 00:48:01.887
Whoa!

722
00:48:03.394 --> 00:48:04.720
It's beautiful.

723
00:48:06.957 --> 00:48:12.321
Long before my time. the lion turtles
granted the gift of bending to humans.

724
00:48:13.421 --> 00:48:15.321
These are their final resting grounds.

725
00:48:16.521 --> 00:48:19.321
This is where Sonam
came to learn their ways.

726
00:48:20.621 --> 00:48:23.321
I am certain that she left her staff here.

727
00:48:23.854 --> 00:48:25.154
Where should we start looking?

728
00:48:25.437 --> 00:48:28.087
Aang. you must connect with her.

729
00:48:29.262 --> 00:48:32.087
But no one can connect with Sonam.

730
00:48:32.353 --> 00:48:35.153
The spiritual power of the lion
turtles is still concentrated here.

731
00:48:36.204 --> 00:48:39.154
Let it guide you.
We'll set out immediately.

732
00:48:39.437 --> 00:48:42.487
Actually. Tagah. we could
really use your help here.

733
00:48:42.820 --> 00:48:45.631
If the denied are close
behind. we need to be ready.

734
00:48:45.828 --> 00:48:49.343
Yeah. and we're gonna need more
than Toph's metal bending to fix this.

735
00:48:49.537 --> 00:48:52.495
My bending got us through that storm.
What did you do?

736
00:48:52.662 --> 00:48:53.662
Steered with his feet.

737
00:48:54.120 --> 00:48:56.820
Repairs can wait. Aang needs me.

738
00:48:57.071 --> 00:49:00.321
Taga. please. stay and help my friends.

739
00:49:01.337 --> 00:49:02.187
I'll be okay on my own.

740
00:49:03.455 --> 00:49:04.861
As you wish.

741
00:49:05.386 --> 00:49:08.095
We will begin repairs for our voyage home.

742
00:49:09.763 --> 00:49:14.101
Everyone. I know I've asked
a lot of you on this journey.

743
00:49:14.255 --> 00:49:18.254
But we're about to accomplish
something that will change the world.

744
00:50:09.322 --> 00:50:10.322
Let it guide you.

745
00:50:27.254 --> 00:50:29.877
Sonam?

746
00:50:46.737 --> 00:50:50.323
Oh. this is turning out
to be a nice little vacation.

747
00:50:50.522 --> 00:50:54.095
Aside from all the people trying
to kill us. and the tornadoes.

748
00:50:54.120 --> 00:50:56.697
Um. we're supposed to be fixing the ship?

749
00:50:56.753 --> 00:50:57.988
You're doing great. buddy.

750
00:50:58.603 --> 00:51:00.750
Has anyone seen Tagah?

751
00:51:00.816 --> 00:51:03.603
Yes. we've all seen Taga. He's so gorgeous.

752
00:51:03.628 --> 00:51:04.995
Geez. I get it.

753
00:51:05.662 --> 00:51:07.273
Oh. I see what you mean.

754
00:51:07.331 --> 00:51:08.468
He wandered off that way.

755
00:51:08.722 --> 00:51:11.184
No. maybe that way?

756
00:51:24.487 --> 00:51:32.487
[MUSIC]

757
00:51:44.701 --> 00:51:45.836
Tagah?

758
00:51:46.602 --> 00:51:48.121
Where are you going?

759
00:51:48.455 --> 00:51:50.563
Aang needs to be protected.

760
00:51:50.588 --> 00:51:51.709
I agree.

761
00:51:54.636 --> 00:51:57.321
I know my ways may seem unusual to you.

762
00:51:57.571 --> 00:52:01.961
But I assure you. everything
I do. I do for Aang.

763
00:52:01.994 --> 00:52:04.805
For Aang? Or for the staff?

764
00:52:06.039 --> 00:52:08.635
You have no idea all that we've lost.

765
00:52:09.021 --> 00:52:11.321
You've never known a world with airbenders.

766
00:52:11.746 --> 00:52:13.321
I know Aang.

767
00:52:14.071 --> 00:52:15.877
He may be the last of his kind.

768
00:52:16.075 --> 00:52:18.621
But he's the reason this world knows peace.

769
00:52:22.265 --> 00:52:26.322
His values as an air nomad
have brought balance to chaos.

770
00:52:26.323 --> 00:52:28.322
[MUSIC]

771
00:52:28.323 --> 00:52:31.582
It's because of Aang
that the Water Tribes.

772
00:52:31.594 --> 00:52:35.322
Earth Kingdom. and Fire
Nation now work together.

773
00:52:35.323 --> 00:52:37.322
Striving for harmony.

774
00:52:37.323 --> 00:52:40.322
A peace we once thought unattainable.

775
00:52:42.701 --> 00:52:44.322
You speak of peace.

776
00:52:44.323 --> 00:52:47.322
There will never be
peace among the elements.

777
00:52:47.323 --> 00:52:48.322
There never was.

778
00:52:48.323 --> 00:52:52.322
Your precious Republic
City is built on lies.

779
00:52:52.323 --> 00:52:54.322
It's built on hope.

780
00:52:54.323 --> 00:52:56.322
Do you have hope. Tagah?

781
00:52:56.323 --> 00:52:59.322
Saving my people requires
more than just hope.

782
00:52:59.397 --> 00:53:01.322
It requires sacrifice.

783
00:53:01.372 --> 00:53:04.322
I saw you try to crush
the denied's airships.

784
00:53:04.397 --> 00:53:05.959
You were ready to kill them.

785
00:53:08.176 --> 00:53:11.055
I know what kind of airbender Aang is.

786
00:53:13.123 --> 00:53:15.592
But what kind of airbender are you?

787
00:53:19.688 --> 00:53:23.783
[MUSIC]

788
00:53:38.817 --> 00:53:43.117
[MUSIC]

789
00:53:44.190 --> 00:53:46.189
Aang did well getting us here.

790
00:53:46.323 --> 00:53:48.334
There is great strength in him...

791
00:53:48.667 --> 00:53:50.368
but weakness as well.

792
00:53:50.497 --> 00:53:51.322
Weakness?

793
00:53:51.513 --> 00:53:52.768
Yes

794
00:53:52.792 --> 00:53:54.096
YOU

795
00:54:04.878 --> 00:54:08.389
[MUSIC]

796
00:54:10.323 --> 00:54:12.322
What the hog monkey?

797
00:54:35.247 --> 00:54:37.675
He trusted you.

798
00:54:43.821 --> 00:54:44.821
No.

799
00:54:48.644 --> 00:54:50.005
[ distant ] Traitor!

800
00:55:01.483 --> 00:55:02.664
[MUSIC]

801
00:55:09.783 --> 00:55:13.383
[MUSIC]

802
00:55:15.588 --> 00:55:21.311
[MUSIC]

803
00:55:27.322 --> 00:55:30.759
[MUSIC]

804
00:55:35.610 --> 00:55:37.243
[MUSIC]

805
00:55:43.988 --> 00:55:47.310
[MUSIC]

806
00:56:05.163 --> 00:56:06.414
Brother.

807
00:56:09.313 --> 00:56:12.637
Tagah. it's real.

808
00:56:16.323 --> 00:56:18.767
We can finally bring back airbending.

809
00:56:21.323 --> 00:56:23.322
Let's go tell the others.

810
00:56:23.323 --> 00:56:26.233
We can do this. me and you.

811
00:56:27.223 --> 00:56:29.386
I can't do this without my friends.

812
00:56:31.323 --> 00:56:34.322
Earth killed my people. fire killed yours.

813
00:56:34.621 --> 00:56:38.121
The staff is the only way we
can create a new air empire.

814
00:56:38.554 --> 00:56:40.924
One capable of defending itself.

815
00:56:41.091 --> 00:56:41.847
No...

816
00:56:41.871 --> 00:56:44.322
we can build a new future. Tagah.

817
00:56:44.347 --> 00:56:46.147
But it has to be for everyone.

818
00:56:46.397 --> 00:56:48.322
The staff doesn't belong to everyone.

819
00:56:48.622 --> 00:56:50.322
It belongs to us.

820
00:56:50.323 --> 00:56:51.984
What have you done?

821
00:56:52.109 --> 00:56:55.287
As long as they were around. you
always put them ahead of our people.

822
00:56:55.980 --> 00:56:57.155
Don't you see?

823
00:56:57.323 --> 00:56:59.434
This is how we redeem ourselves.

824
00:56:59.734 --> 00:57:01.322
It doesn't matter that you ran then.

825
00:57:01.774 --> 00:57:03.834
As long as you stand with me now.

826
00:57:03.904 --> 00:57:04.279
No...

827
00:57:04.325 --> 00:57:05.967
Aang. listen to me.

828
00:57:06.007 --> 00:57:06.873
Katara!

829
00:57:06.898 --> 00:57:08.105
This is the only way.

830
00:57:08.282 --> 00:57:08.905
...no...

831
00:57:14.410 --> 00:57:16.933
[MUSIC]

832
00:57:22.323 --> 00:57:24.322
You're a traitor to your own.

833
00:57:24.323 --> 00:57:26.323
Just like Sonam.

834
00:57:28.656 --> 00:57:30.169
[MUSIC]

835
00:57:45.419 --> 00:57:49.775
[SCREAMING]

836
00:58:03.877 --> 00:58:06.876
I wanted to do this with you by my side.

837
00:58:07.590 --> 00:58:10.602
But if I must build
a new air empire alone...

838
00:58:11.052 --> 00:58:12.366
so be it.

839
00:58:21.324 --> 00:58:22.323
There's no way in.

840
00:58:22.324 --> 00:58:24.195
We have to turn back.

841
00:58:24.220 --> 00:58:27.212
No. we keep trying to push through.

842
00:58:39.324 --> 00:58:40.543
Sonam's staff.

843
00:58:41.819 --> 00:58:43.323
Denied.

844
00:58:43.324 --> 00:58:45.323
The Avatar is dead.

845
00:58:45.324 --> 00:58:50.323
If you wish to build a new world where
you have the power. I can give it to you.

846
00:59:05.410 --> 00:59:06.434
Appa.

847
00:59:06.828 --> 00:59:08.078
Katara.

848
00:59:08.757 --> 00:59:10.107
Katara!

849
00:59:11.079 --> 00:59:12.018
Katara.

850
00:59:13.298 --> 00:59:14.553
They're gone.

851
00:59:15.133 --> 00:59:16.795
It's all my fault.

852
00:59:17.306 --> 00:59:19.056
It's always been my fault.

853
00:59:19.706 --> 00:59:21.973
Ever since I ran away.

854
00:59:23.295 --> 00:59:29.777
No Avatar has ever fallen into such
shame as to join me here in my sorrow.

855
00:59:31.190 --> 00:59:32.914
Why do you grieve so. friend?

856
00:59:33.800 --> 00:59:35.741
Avatar Sonam?

857
00:59:38.355 --> 00:59:40.055
Tagah murdered my friends.

858
00:59:40.628 --> 00:59:42.078
And now he has the staff.

859
00:59:42.324 --> 00:59:43.323
Tagah.

860
00:59:43.324 --> 00:59:44.323
No.

861
00:59:44.348 --> 00:59:45.207
No. I...

862
00:59:45.232 --> 00:59:46.692
I stopped him.

863
00:59:47.183 --> 00:59:48.510
I hid the staff.

864
00:59:49.273 --> 00:59:51.437
What have you done?

865
00:59:52.123 --> 00:59:54.122
You're the one who gave him airbending.

866
00:59:54.628 --> 00:59:57.078
How could you give power to a monster?

867
00:59:57.649 --> 01:00:01.655
The Tagah I gave bending
to was a different man.

868
01:00:02.324 --> 01:00:05.323
It was a different time.

869
01:00:05.373 --> 01:00:08.323
The airbenders were the
peacekeepers of the four elements.

870
01:00:08.840 --> 01:00:13.190
We used our power to mediate
all conflict with nonviolence.

871
01:00:13.339 --> 01:00:15.807
But we were the fewest in numbers.

872
01:00:16.324 --> 01:00:21.323
For many years. we existed in a
beautiful balance of great prosperity.

873
01:00:21.500 --> 01:00:24.100
But the world began to shift.

874
01:00:24.125 --> 01:00:29.124
The earthbenders formed their own kingdom.
separating from the other elemental tribes.

875
01:00:29.523 --> 01:00:32.323
The balance of the world was at risk.

876
01:00:32.523 --> 01:00:35.323
It was my duty to act.

877
01:00:35.324 --> 01:00:37.445
So I learned how to
channel the energy of the

878
01:00:37.470 --> 01:00:39.884
spirit world just as
the lion turtles did.

879
01:00:40.372 --> 01:00:43.703
To give people the power of airbending.

880
01:00:44.079 --> 01:00:49.078
My most devout pupil.
Tagah. was the first to receive it.

881
01:00:49.623 --> 01:00:54.123
I sent my new peacekeepers out
to help calm the growing unrest.

882
01:00:54.772 --> 01:01:00.610
But they were not prepared for the
brutality of the new earth kingdom.

883
01:01:01.324 --> 01:01:06.448
Tagah watched as his brothers
and sisters were all slaughtered.

884
01:01:07.575 --> 01:01:10.105
His heart darkened by the violence of war.

885
01:01:10.798 --> 01:01:15.366
He now saw everyone who
wasn't an air nomad as the enemy.

886
01:01:16.233 --> 01:01:18.676
Tagah begged me to
use the staff to create an

887
01:01:18.701 --> 01:01:21.046
army and to kill all
who would do us harm.

888
01:01:21.434 --> 01:01:23.198
I refused.

889
01:01:23.588 --> 01:01:25.152
So he stole it.

890
01:01:26.057 --> 01:01:28.458
When he connected
the staff to the temple.

891
01:01:28.483 --> 01:01:31.069
his energy was so
corrupted by grief and rage

892
01:01:31.094 --> 01:01:35.093
that the power of the
spirit world consumed him.

893
01:01:35.118 --> 01:01:41.117
Tagah became something more
than human. too powerful to kill.

894
01:01:41.142 --> 01:01:44.325
It took all my energy
to finally trap him high

895
01:01:44.350 --> 01:01:47.732
above the clouds where
no one would find him.

896
01:01:48.551 --> 01:01:52.749
I reclaimed the staff.
but I was fatally wounded.

897
01:01:53.305 --> 01:01:56.108
Before the earth kingdom
could invade Jirana. I

898
01:01:56.133 --> 01:01:59.068
sent the remaining air
nomads into the mountains.

899
01:01:59.548 --> 01:02:04.609
And I hid my temple in the spirit world
where no one could access its power.

900
01:02:06.251 --> 01:02:12.101
Then I locked the staff away
where only the avatar could find it.

901
01:02:12.324 --> 01:02:16.465
I died hoping that one day
another avatar would create

902
01:02:16.477 --> 01:02:20.323
more airbenders and
restore balance to this world.

903
01:02:20.775 --> 01:02:23.500
And that avatar is you. Aang.

904
01:02:23.545 --> 01:02:27.146
You have to get my staff before
Tagah connects it to the temple.

905
01:02:27.640 --> 01:02:31.190
There's still time.
Don't let my regret become yours.

906
01:02:31.923 --> 01:02:34.123
My friends and I fought
hard for this peace.

907
01:02:34.995 --> 01:02:37.145
I won't let him start another war.

908
01:02:37.170 --> 01:02:40.169
Help me find a way back.

909
01:02:40.194 --> 01:02:42.193
Sonam?

910
01:02:43.106 --> 01:02:44.106
What's happening?

911
01:02:46.271 --> 01:02:48.445
No! No!

912
01:02:48.470 --> 01:02:50.430
Please! I have to fix this!

913
01:02:50.694 --> 01:02:55.455
This can't be it! I can't die yet!
Please! Not yet! No!

914
01:02:55.480 --> 01:02:56.730
- Aang? - Katara?

915
01:02:56.754 --> 01:02:57.701
[ distant ]  I'm losing him

916
01:02:57.725 --> 01:03:02.128
Come on. Aang! Come on!
Aang! Hold on!

917
01:03:02.152 --> 01:03:03.891
 Aang!

918
01:03:04.962 --> 01:03:07.212
- Katara. - I was so worried.

919
01:03:07.634 --> 01:03:12.434
Aang. Sokka.
I knew you'd pull through. buddy.

920
01:03:12.774 --> 01:03:14.324
- Hey. Aang. - Zuko.

921
01:03:14.724 --> 01:03:18.324
- Momo. - Welcome back. Twinkle Toes.

922
01:03:18.415 --> 01:03:23.077
Toph. you're okay.
I thought you were all dead.

923
01:03:23.102 --> 01:03:26.221
We were. but Katara saved us.

924
01:03:26.618 --> 01:03:32.168
The spiritual power of these waters
strengthened my healing abilities.

925
01:03:33.191 --> 01:03:35.617
You're incredible. Katara.

926
01:03:36.857 --> 01:03:38.231
Where's Appa?

927
01:03:39.529 --> 01:03:41.079
Tagah must have taken him.

928
01:03:41.893 --> 01:03:42.968
I'm sorry.

929
01:03:43.318 --> 01:03:44.968
No.

930
01:03:45.902 --> 01:03:49.102
I can't believe I trusted him.

931
01:03:49.779 --> 01:03:52.079
We'll get through this.

932
01:03:54.118 --> 01:03:55.278
So. let me get this straight.

933
01:03:56.007 --> 01:04:00.677
He's pulling Sonam's temple out of
the spirit world to gain unlimited power?

934
01:04:00.702 --> 01:04:03.701
And let me guess. you want us to stop him?

935
01:04:04.057 --> 01:04:09.057
Sure. Only problem is your air bro
crushed our ship and stole your bison.

936
01:04:09.235 --> 01:04:13.035
Also. there's a massive
typhoon surrounding us!

937
01:04:15.876 --> 01:04:18.789
I don't say this very
often. but Sokka's right.

938
01:04:19.055 --> 01:04:21.324
- Thank you. - Yep. we're stuck.

939
01:04:21.435 --> 01:04:24.235
And there aren't enough lion turtles
for all of us to have our own island.

940
01:04:24.325 --> 01:04:27.324
So. I'm calling this one.
I'm naming him Snappy.

941
01:04:27.374 --> 01:04:31.324
- Aw. Snappy is the best one. - I know.

942
01:04:31.390 --> 01:04:34.088
We may not know where
Tagah is. but we know

943
01:04:34.113 --> 01:04:37.012
what he's looking for
is in the spirit world.

944
01:04:37.504 --> 01:04:42.079
And lucky for us. we're stuck in the most
spiritually charged place on the planet.

945
01:04:42.851 --> 01:04:49.101
So. I may be able to open a portal to get
us there. if I can summon an old friend.

946
01:04:57.340 --> 01:04:58.437
Wow.

947
01:04:59.151 --> 01:05:00.770
The ocean spirit.

948
01:05:08.821 --> 01:05:11.324
This portal smells an
awful lot like the fish market.

949
01:05:11.325 --> 01:05:13.324
I'm gonna go check on Snappy.

950
01:05:13.474 --> 01:05:15.324
Face your death with honor.

951
01:05:15.374 --> 01:05:20.324
I'm sorry. I know I got us into
this. but I promise you I'll fix it.

952
01:05:20.724 --> 01:05:22.723
We'll fix it.

953
01:05:22.902 --> 01:05:24.901
Together.

954
01:05:27.393 --> 01:05:30.435
We're gonna die! We're gonna die!

955
01:05:40.028 --> 01:05:40.544
What?

956
01:05:40.678 --> 01:05:42.595
 Where's my power pony?

957
01:05:42.839 --> 01:05:45.279
Were my hands always this small?

958
01:05:45.413 --> 01:05:48.412
It's baby Toph! Baby Toph!

959
01:05:49.284 --> 01:05:51.144
What the hog monkey?

960
01:05:51.168 --> 01:05:52.695
Ah! Old people!

961
01:05:52.720 --> 01:05:53.453
Gran Gran?

962
01:05:53.540 --> 01:05:55.539
It's your sister. you meat head!

963
01:05:55.676 --> 01:05:58.300
Give me Toph. There. there. Toph.

964
01:05:58.325 --> 01:06:01.324
Oh no. Zuko!
What happened to your beautiful face?

965
01:06:01.658 --> 01:06:04.082
You look like a dried sea squid.

966
01:06:04.260 --> 01:06:05.324
No. Zuko!

967
01:06:05.325 --> 01:06:06.518
tired...

968
01:06:06.543 --> 01:06:08.094
What's going on here?

969
01:06:09.032 --> 01:06:11.324
The spirit world is out of balance.

970
01:06:11.896 --> 01:06:12.946
And so are we.

971
01:06:15.479 --> 01:06:16.753
That's gotta be Tagah.

972
01:06:39.136 --> 01:06:40.113
Oh no!

973
01:06:40.345 --> 01:06:42.789
He's pulling Sonam's
temple into our world!

974
01:06:42.814 --> 01:06:44.608
We're running out of time!

975
01:06:51.969 --> 01:06:53.690
Pretty good landing.

976
01:06:54.124 --> 01:06:57.189
Whoa! Humans! I love humans!

977
01:06:57.214 --> 01:06:59.989
Two brothers. their little
sister. and an elderly couple.

978
01:07:00.013 --> 01:07:00.762
[ together ]  A COUPLE?

979
01:07:00.787 --> 01:07:01.811
Not a couple!

980
01:07:01.835 --> 01:07:03.834
Whoa! Looks like I touched a nerve.

981
01:07:04.224 --> 01:07:07.124
Oh. look at this one! Hello!

982
01:07:07.149 --> 01:07:09.148
Toph! No! Bad Toph!

983
01:07:09.325 --> 01:07:11.324
We don't bite strangers.

984
01:07:12.324 --> 01:07:16.324
Great spirit! Excuse me. did you
just come from that temple in the sky?

985
01:07:16.325 --> 01:07:18.324
I certainly did.

986
01:07:18.325 --> 01:07:20.324
It was my favorite hidey hole.

987
01:07:20.325 --> 01:07:23.324
Until that dark. yucky energy
started corrupting this whole place.

988
01:07:23.874 --> 01:07:27.325
Please. we need your help getting up there.

989
01:07:27.326 --> 01:07:29.325
It's my duty to stop this.

990
01:07:29.525 --> 01:07:31.325
I'm the Avatar.

991
01:07:31.575 --> 01:07:35.325
Ooh! The Avatar!

992
01:07:35.425 --> 01:07:37.092
Let me have a squiz at you.

993
01:07:37.117 --> 01:07:38.967
Okay. now with this eye.

994
01:07:39.138 --> 01:07:40.513
And this eye.

995
01:07:40.538 --> 01:07:42.089
Ooh. don't forget this eye.

996
01:07:42.114 --> 01:07:43.009
Can we hurry it up?

997
01:07:43.034 --> 01:07:44.033
... have a squiz.

998
01:07:44.326 --> 01:07:46.325
Sniff check!

999
01:07:48.058 --> 01:07:50.133
Ooh. that's Avatar material right there.

1000
01:07:50.158 --> 01:07:52.157
Yes. it is. Oh!

1001
01:07:52.326 --> 01:07:53.325
Yes. yes. yes. yes. yes!

1002
01:07:53.326 --> 01:07:58.325
It appears the universe has brought
us together for a very important mission.

1003
01:08:00.529 --> 01:08:02.325
To flee!

1004
01:08:02.326 --> 01:08:04.325
Run for your lives!

1005
01:08:04.326 --> 01:08:05.412
Wait! Come back!

1006
01:08:05.437 --> 01:08:07.098
You're going the wrong way!

1007
01:08:07.123 --> 01:08:08.122
Stop!

1008
01:08:08.147 --> 01:08:10.262
Please. great spirit. both
of our worlds are in danger.

1009
01:08:10.287 --> 01:08:13.170
No. no. no. no. no. no.
I am not going back up there.

1010
01:08:19.449 --> 01:08:22.588
Hmm. well. when you put it like
that. it does make more sense.

1011
01:08:23.652 --> 01:08:27.628
Upon reflection. I've decided I shall
help you and your human-y friends.

1012
01:08:27.720 --> 01:08:29.214
What did he say?

1013
01:08:29.239 --> 01:08:30.238
Nice work. Momo.

1014
01:08:30.350 --> 01:08:32.349
Alright. in you go.

1015
01:08:35.278 --> 01:08:38.667
By the way. no eating anything you find
in my teeth. as I'm saving that for later.

1016
01:08:39.068 --> 01:08:41.325
Ready. set. get steady and rest.

1017
01:08:41.326 --> 01:08:44.325
One and the two and
the you know what to do.

1018
01:08:44.326 --> 01:08:45.661
Blast off!

1019
01:08:50.747 --> 01:08:54.933
I know we haven't known each
other very long. but I love you!

1020
01:08:54.991 --> 01:08:56.816
You don't have to say it back.

1021
01:09:04.946 --> 01:09:06.946
Hey! You got your hair back!

1022
01:09:06.971 --> 01:09:09.970
Why are my eyes teary? Was I crying?

1023
01:09:10.425 --> 01:09:12.325
No way! Look!

1024
01:09:12.478 --> 01:09:14.103
What? What is it?

1025
01:09:14.158 --> 01:09:16.157
It's Republic City.

1026
01:09:19.122 --> 01:09:22.325
We can't let him destroy
everything we've built.

1027
01:09:22.350 --> 01:09:23.746
We won't.

1028
01:09:38.812 --> 01:09:40.283
Boomerang!

1029
01:09:57.373 --> 01:09:59.175
Give me the staff. Tagah!

1030
01:09:59.200 --> 01:10:01.199
I see I underestimated you. Avatar.

1031
01:10:01.952 --> 01:10:04.325
Your friends are stronger than I thought.

1032
01:10:04.326 --> 01:10:06.325
But you're too late.

1033
01:10:14.126 --> 01:10:15.325
The Denied.

1034
01:10:15.914 --> 01:10:18.617
You see. I did what you wanted. Aang.

1035
01:10:18.728 --> 01:10:21.638
I returned airbending to the world.

1036
01:10:23.172 --> 01:10:24.325
What's the plan?

1037
01:10:24.356 --> 01:10:27.081
We'll deal with the Denied.
You have to get the staff.

1038
01:10:27.814 --> 01:10:32.631
I will rebuild Jirana on the ruins
of our enemies. just as they did on ours.

1039
01:10:32.703 --> 01:10:35.582
A new air empire will rise.

1040
01:10:35.837 --> 01:10:37.702
Kill them all.

1041
01:10:55.598 --> 01:10:58.325
We have to get these people out of here.

1042
01:11:02.147 --> 01:11:04.147
Whoa!

1043
01:11:14.284 --> 01:11:15.565
Oh. yeah.

1044
01:11:22.922 --> 01:11:23.969
Tagah!

1045
01:11:24.058 --> 01:11:25.301
Give it to me!

1046
01:11:27.531 --> 01:11:31.325
This isn't the way. We can use
the staff to bring back balance.

1047
01:11:31.326 --> 01:11:32.172
Peace!

1048
01:11:32.197 --> 01:11:36.435
You care so much about your
ideals that you'd let your people die!

1049
01:11:36.636 --> 01:11:40.635
I will do anything to
make sure they survive!

1050
01:11:57.570 --> 01:12:01.569
Not my cabbages! Not my cabbages!

1051
01:12:06.027 --> 01:12:11.325
My cabbages! My cabbages!

1052
01:12:23.823 --> 01:12:25.326
Don't do this.

1053
01:12:25.468 --> 01:12:26.423
You have the power now.

1054
01:12:26.534 --> 01:12:28.326
You can decide how to use it.

1055
01:12:28.462 --> 01:12:31.074
I'm not like you.
The world hasn't been good to me.

1056
01:12:31.193 --> 01:12:33.051
The world is what we make it.

1057
01:12:33.148 --> 01:12:35.147
Get away from her!

1058
01:13:06.744 --> 01:13:08.744
Tagah! Stop!

1059
01:13:13.119 --> 01:13:15.613
You betrayed me! You betrayed our culture!

1060
01:13:15.638 --> 01:13:18.637
I gave you every chance to see the truth!

1061
01:13:23.857 --> 01:13:26.302
Shouldn't you be in the Fire Nation?

1062
01:13:28.334 --> 01:13:30.326
I'm fighting for the peace of all nations.

1063
01:13:34.135 --> 01:13:38.326
Big talk from someone who sits
on a throne built on a century of war!

1064
01:14:00.858 --> 01:14:03.958
I'm still the greatest
earthbender in the world!

1065
01:14:28.228 --> 01:14:29.332
Oh no!

1066
01:14:29.376 --> 01:14:30.466
I'm out of water!

1067
01:14:33.635 --> 01:14:34.554
We got ya!

1068
01:14:34.953 --> 01:14:37.735
And there's no Avatar here to save you.

1069
01:14:39.308 --> 01:14:41.326
Sokka cycle!

1070
01:14:44.921 --> 01:14:49.326
Let's see if your fancy new bending can
beat some good ol' non-bending know-how!

1071
01:14:56.072 --> 01:14:58.389
Bombs away!

1072
01:15:04.670 --> 01:15:06.326
You just got denied!

1073
01:15:15.211 --> 01:15:15.925
Let's go!

1074
01:15:15.950 --> 01:15:17.949
Good luck saving your city!

1075
01:15:26.481 --> 01:15:29.205
We have to save as many people as we can!

1076
01:15:47.352 --> 01:15:50.817
I know your pain.
I know what you've been through.

1077
01:15:51.377 --> 01:15:53.326
You don't know.

1078
01:15:53.676 --> 01:15:57.861
I watched as all of my brothers
and sisters were slaughtered.

1079
01:15:58.456 --> 01:16:01.924
And the Fire Nation burned
the Air Nomads to ash!

1080
01:16:02.191 --> 01:16:04.077
Where were you?

1081
01:16:04.215 --> 01:16:05.871
You ran!

1082
01:16:26.243 --> 01:16:28.243
Tagah!

1083
01:16:37.659 --> 01:16:39.273
No!

1084
01:17:01.147 --> 01:17:07.353
The full power of the Spirit
World flows through me!

1085
01:17:16.347 --> 01:17:18.735
This is what strength looks like!

1086
01:18:12.207 --> 01:18:17.737
You should've run away like you
did all those years ago. little Avatar.

1087
01:18:17.959 --> 01:18:22.327
I... won't... run.

1088
01:18:22.328 --> 01:18:26.327
Then at least you'll die knowing
you're not the last Airbender!

1089
01:19:12.681 --> 01:19:13.681
No!

1090
01:20:20.640 --> 01:20:22.742
We could've been brothers!

1091
01:20:22.936 --> 01:20:25.480
We could've done this together!

1092
01:20:25.505 --> 01:20:27.504
It didn't have to end like this!

1093
01:20:32.845 --> 01:20:34.557
It's Aang. He's got the staff!

1094
01:20:34.670 --> 01:20:36.669
Yeah! Kick his butt. Mega Aang!

1095
01:20:36.883 --> 01:20:40.882
No! Something's wrong!
The power is corrupting him!

1096
01:20:58.637 --> 01:21:02.860
I dreamt of bringing the Air Nomads
back to the world as peacekeepers.

1097
01:21:02.885 --> 01:21:06.327
They could've been a beacon
of light for the world to follow.

1098
01:21:06.328 --> 01:21:10.520
But you ruined it!
You twisted my dream into a nightmare!

1099
01:21:10.545 --> 01:21:14.327
Finally.
You have the power the Air Nomads need.

1100
01:21:14.328 --> 01:21:17.327
Maybe there is hope for you after all.

1101
01:21:27.666 --> 01:21:33.900
Do it! Use the staff! Show me you have
the strength to bring our people back!

1102
01:21:34.589 --> 01:21:35.605
Do it!

1103
01:22:12.348 --> 01:22:13.348
Aang...

1104
01:22:16.177 --> 01:22:19.405
You will do so many
great things as the Avatar.

1105
01:22:20.077 --> 01:22:23.805
But you must be prepared to
do what frightens you the most.

1106
01:22:25.417 --> 01:22:31.135
Your people. your home.
we are always with you.

1107
01:22:46.616 --> 01:22:47.616
No!

1108
01:23:18.512 --> 01:23:20.677
No! My power!

1109
01:23:27.405 --> 01:23:30.074
No. No!

1110
01:23:39.506 --> 01:23:44.720
You fool! Why? Why did you break it?

1111
01:23:45.209 --> 01:23:47.950
We could've fixed everything.

1112
01:23:49.083 --> 01:23:51.794
We can't erase the pain of the past.

1113
01:23:52.550 --> 01:23:53.838
We couldn't save them.

1114
01:23:54.070 --> 01:23:57.927
But it's our duty to protect our people.

1115
01:23:58.194 --> 01:24:01.523
Not at the cost of betraying
everything they stood for.

1116
01:24:01.656 --> 01:24:02.611
No.

1117
01:24:03.189 --> 01:24:04.839
It's time to let go.

1118
01:24:05.822 --> 01:24:08.491
You have to forgive yourself.

1119
01:24:10.293 --> 01:24:12.707
I have to forgive myself too.

1120
01:24:21.483 --> 01:24:24.523
Air Nomads are formed from the mist.

1121
01:24:28.324 --> 01:24:33.518
We walk the world for a moment in time.

1122
01:24:34.838 --> 01:24:39.838
Then we return to the eternal wind.

1123
01:24:55.190 --> 01:24:56.526
Aang!

1124
01:25:00.212 --> 01:25:01.328
Hey. Katara.

1125
01:25:02.006 --> 01:25:03.106
Hey. Aang.

1126
01:25:05.439 --> 01:25:06.439
Seriously?

1127
01:25:06.804 --> 01:25:09.507
You do realize you're falling. right?

1128
01:25:09.649 --> 01:25:11.481
Hey. if you ever get
tired of relying on Appa.

1129
01:25:11.506 --> 01:25:13.505
I could hook you up with
one of these babies.

1130
01:25:18.728 --> 01:25:21.702
I'll give you the best friend discount!

1131
01:25:35.183 --> 01:25:37.083
I don't know if
airbending will ever return.

1132
01:25:38.322 --> 01:25:41.172
But I know now that the
true power of the Air Nomads

1133
01:25:41.927 --> 01:25:43.127
was never their bending.

1134
01:25:43.677 --> 01:25:45.127
It was their values.

1135
01:25:45.849 --> 01:25:48.149
And that's a power I can pass on to others.

1136
01:25:49.427 --> 01:25:54.127
Avatar Aang. you are the true
embodiment of the Air Nomads.

1137
01:25:55.327 --> 01:25:58.437
Thank you for giving up
the power that I could not.

1138
01:25:59.525 --> 01:26:02.150
You give me hope for
the future of our culture.

1139
01:26:03.616 --> 01:26:05.616
[music playing]

1140
01:26:16.216 --> 01:26:18.235
It's amazing. isn't it?

1141
01:26:18.702 --> 01:26:21.613
The first new air temple in centuries.

1142
01:26:22.729 --> 01:26:26.272
Republic City is finally complete.

1143
01:26:29.378 --> 01:26:33.328
A city for all nations.
just like you promised.

1144
01:26:33.877 --> 01:26:36.127
I never could have done
this without you. Katara.

1145
01:26:37.805 --> 01:26:40.105
Hey. everybody.
Sorry I kept you all waiting.

1146
01:26:40.783 --> 01:26:42.083
Are you ready for our big trip?

1147
01:26:43.768 --> 01:26:45.503
As my new acolytes.

1148
01:26:45.528 --> 01:26:49.328
you'll be helping me preserve
our culture for future generations.

1149
01:26:49.329 --> 01:26:50.490
So...

1150
01:26:50.690 --> 01:26:54.149
who wants to search for artifacts
at an ancient abandoned temple?

1151
01:26:54.174 --> 01:26:55.174
Yay.

1152
01:26:55.349 --> 01:26:59.229
I'm only going to make sure you don't
try to release another beefy old airbender.

1153
01:26:59.329 --> 01:27:01.447
Yeah. I'm done with bad boys.

1154
01:27:03.328 --> 01:27:05.328
[music playing]

1155
01:27:13.700 --> 01:27:16.328
Avatar Sonam told me about this place.

1156
01:27:16.378 --> 01:27:20.128
so it's very possible that no one's
been here in hundreds of years.

1157
01:27:21.461 --> 01:27:24.062
Oh. is this an airbender relic?

1158
01:27:24.404 --> 01:27:26.129
I think that's just a rock.

1159
01:27:26.156 --> 01:27:28.106
But I love the enthusiasm.

1160
01:27:29.492 --> 01:27:30.305
Oh.

1161
01:27:30.381 --> 01:27:32.329
[screaming]

1162
01:27:34.017 --> 01:27:35.217
Keep your eyes open.

1163
01:27:35.384 --> 01:27:37.104
You never know what we might discover here.

1164
01:27:38.618 --> 01:27:40.218
Oh.

1165
01:27:46.889 --> 01:27:48.445
I thought they were extinct.

1166
01:27:55.728 --> 01:27:57.473
I can't believe it.

1167
01:27:57.730 --> 01:27:59.729
The original airbenders.

1168
01:28:01.639 --> 01:28:03.639
[roaring]

1169
01:28:07.068 --> 01:28:09.329
Oh. can I have one?

1170
01:28:09.330 --> 01:28:10.329
[laughing]

1171
01:28:10.330 --> 01:28:12.329
Appa. yip yip!

1172
